        "title": "feat(durable): expose gateway and CLI lifecycle",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThis PR exposes the durable workflow kernel through OpenClaw Gateway and CLI lifecycle paths.\n\nIt adds:\n\n- durable agent turn lifecycle recording;\n- durable gateway startup record and startup reconciliation;\n- recovery worker startup hook;\n- `openclaw durable` CLI inspection commands;\n- `durable.coordination.get` gateway read API;\n- gateway protocol documentation.\n\n## Why\n\nThe kernel is useful only if accepted agent work becomes visible in normal OpenClaw runtime paths. This PR records agent turns durably and gives operators a native inspection path.\n\n## Stack Note\n\nThis is PR 3 in the durable core stack and should be reviewed after PR 1 and PR 2.\n\nGitHub may show cumulative diff until previous PRs are merged because the branch is pushed from a fork and the upstream repository does not allow branch bases for this stack.\n\nIncremental branch:\n\n- `mjnkao:codex/openclaw-x-durable-pr3-gateway-cli`\n\n## Validation\n\n- `npm test -- --run src/durable src/gateway/server-methods/durable.test.ts extensions/workboard/src/gateway.test.ts extensions/workboard/src/store.test.ts`\n- `npm run tsgo:core`\n- `npm run build`\n",
